text: Kyzlar-Birgan () is a rural locality (a village) and the administrative center of Urkassky Selsoviet, Zilairsky District, Bashkortostan, Russia. The population was 350 as of 2010. There are 6 streets. == Geography == It is located 74 km from Zilair. == References == Category:Rural localities in Zilairsky District
title: Kyzlar-Birgan
